      },
      "id": "mark_1783513861749_o6dcb",
      "text": "Bringing This Back to Two Pointers\nTwo-pointer problems become much easier once you stop memorizing pointer motion and start asking:\n\nwhat must still be true after these pointers move?\n\nThat is why invariants are worth learning as a general tool first.",
      "url": "https://algo.monster/problems/two_pointers_invariants"
    },
    {
      "color": "#134515",
      "createdAt": 1783574657317,
      "highlightSource": {
        "endMeta": {
          "parentDomPath": [
